    {
      "title": "Convert g values to f values",
      "content": "Since $g(x)=\\frac{f(x)}{x+3}$, multiply each $g(x)$ value by $x+3$ to get $f(x)$.<br/>$$f(-21)=2(-21+3)=-36$$<br/>$$f(-9)=0(-9+3)=0$$<br/>$$f(15)=4(15+3)=72$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Find the linear function",
      "content": "Using points $(-9,0)$ and $(15,72)$, the slope is<br/>$$m=\\frac{72-0}{15-(-9)}=\\frac{72}{24}=3$$<br/>Use $f(x)=3x+b$ and $f(-9)=0$.<br/>$$0=3(-9)+b$$<br/>$$b=27$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Identify the intercept",
      "content": "The $y$-intercept of $y=f(x)$ is $(0,b)$, so the intercept is $(0,27)$. The answer is <strong>D</strong>."
    }
  ]
